Ndaba Mandela attends the Tribeca Disruptive Innovation Awards - 2019 Tribeca Film Festival at BMCC Tribeca PAC on May 03, 2019 in New York City. JOHANNESBURG - Ndaba Mandela has revealed that he has tested positive for COVID-19. Posting a second video on Instagram, Ndaba said he was taking the situation very seriously after receiving backlash for posting an initial video where he announced his results, titled "I got got by the #coronavirus". "I believe that this situation that we have here today with the coronavirus, is a situation that provides us as humanity an opportunity to come together and support one another. READ: Idris Elba tests positive for coronavirus To also remind each other about how we live as a society and our impact on the Earth", said Ndaba. The entrepreneur and author encouraged his followers to ensure that they remain calm and adhere to the guidelines in order to ensure that they remain calm. "Stressing is not going to make a difference and so I urge you not to stress. I urge you not to get anxiety", he added.